		<div class="comment-body"><p>@KAM &#8211; The problem is, rail does not run to every store (nor would it be possible to do so). Trucks have to pick up the goods from the rail terminals and bring them the rest of the way on their journey. Also, due to the limited scheduling capacity, it is hard to get shipments across country at a priority. Rail is an important part of distribution of goods. But, in the modern world, trucks are even more important.</p>
</div>

