		<div class="comment-body"><p>@Timothy Covington,</p>
<p>What you say is correct, and I did mention local trucking in combination with rail shipping.  </p>
<p>Trucks are definitely important, but so is rail, and I see no reason they shouldn&#8217;t be seen as complimentary rather than competitive in most areas.  As most people could probably confirm, many trains run with container loads which are easily transferred to trucks for local delivery.  </p>
<p>My core point is that we all partially subsidize trucking as roads are (mostly) public compared to railroads that are (mostly) privately owned and maintained.</p>
